                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.516 Export Import Bank/10–1347:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Peru</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-30T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 30, 1947—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>549. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtels</gloss> 733 Oct 10, 738 Oct 13.<note n="28"
                        xml:id="d870fn1">Latter not printed.</note> Maffry <gloss
                        target="#t_Eximbank1">Eximbank</gloss> Oct 29 informed Peru Commercial
                    Counselor by letter that “Board Directors has given new consideration to matter
                    (reference Bank’s letter Sep 23<note n="29" xml:id="d870fn2">Letter from the
                        Export-Import Bank to the Peruvian Commercial Counselor, referred to in the
                        Ambassador’s telegram 733, October 10, <ref target="#pg_1013">p.
                        1013</ref>.</note>) and has reviewed with Dept conversations held with
                    Formin in July regarding offer settlement made by Peru Govt to holders its
                    defaulted obligations. Dept has informed Bank that these conversations removed
                    obstacle which had heretofore stood in way consideration by Bank of Peru loan
                    applications. Accordingly Bank is prepared consider proposals for financing
                    projects in Peru on their individual merits”.</p>
                <p>You may inform Peru Govt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
